## 14. STEAM & PUBLISHING

### 14.1 Steam Integration — P1
- [ ] Steam Achievements list (recommendation: 50-80 achievements):
  - Story progression: 1 per zone completed (7)
  - Endings: 1 per ending (5-6)
  - Combat: kill milestones, boss-specific challenges, pacifist run
  - Exploration: all collectibles per type, all secret cars, all cars visited
  - Social: max loyalty with each companion, max rep with each faction
  - Challenges: speedrun, no-death, minimal combat, Kronole-free, full addiction
- [ ] Steam Cloud saves
- [ ] Steam trading cards (if applicable)
- [ ] Steam Workshop support (for mods — see 14.3)
- [ ] Rich Presence: show current zone, playtime, completion % in Steam profile

### 14.2 Store Page & Marketing — P2
- [ ] Write Steam store description (short and long)
- [ ] Define minimum system requirements and recommended specs
- [ ] Plan screenshot set: 1 per zone minimum (7), plus combat, crafting, dialogue, exterior
- [ ] Trailer plan: teaser trailer (30-60s), gameplay trailer (2-3min), launch trailer
- [ ] Define Early Access strategy:
  - EA launch with Zones 1-3 (Cars 1-48)?
  - Full launch with all content?
  - EA roadmap if applicable
- [ ] Demo plan: free demo with Cars 1-10 (Tail only)?

### 14.3 Content Rating — P1
- [ ] Identify ESRB/PEGI-relevant content:
  - Violence: melee combat, blood, environmental kills
  - Drug use: Kronole as a core game mechanic
  - Language: profanity level in dialogue
  - Child endangerment: children in the Engine, children's rations theft
  - Cannibalism: referenced in lore (from the film)
  - Mature themes: class warfare, eugenics, human experimentation
- [ ] Target rating: M (Mature) / PEGI 18 — confirm this is acceptable
- [ ] Content warnings on store page
- [ ] Sensitive content toggles in settings (reduce gore, skip disturbing scenes)?

### 14.4 Mod Support — P3
- [ ] Define mod scope: custom cars, custom items, total conversions?
- [ ] Modding tools: custom car editor, item definition files, dialogue scripting
- [ ] Steam Workshop integration for mod distribution
- [ ] Mod load order management

