## 15. TECHNICAL SPECIFICATIONS

### 15.1 Engine Decision — P0
- [ ] **CRITICAL DECISION:** Confirm engine choice and development workflow
  - Option A: UE5 + Editor (requires visual editing, Megascans/Quixel for free assets)
  - Option B: UE5 + procedural generation (all geometry from code, stylized aesthetic)
  - Option C: Godot + procedural (better terminal-only workflow, GDScript/C#)
  - Option D: Custom engine (maximum control, maximum effort)
- [ ] Define art pipeline based on engine choice:
  - If procedural: define modular geometry kit (wall panels, floor tiles, door frames, furniture blocks)
  - If UE5: define Megascans material palette per zone
  - If Godot: define shader/material approach

### 15.2 Save System — P0
- [ ] Save file format: JSON? Binary? SQLite?
- [ ] Save data per car: NPC states, loot collected, doors opened, faction control, environmental changes
- [ ] Global save data: player stats, inventory, quest progress, faction rep, choice flags, companion states
- [ ] Save slot count: 3 manual saves + 1 autosave? More?
- [ ] Autosave triggers: car entry, quest completion, major choice, timed interval
- [ ] Save file size budget per slot
- [ ] Save file versioning for patches/updates
- [ ] Cloud save format compatible with Steam Cloud

### 15.3 Car Streaming Architecture — P0
- [ ] Define car loading strategy: max 3 cars in memory (current + 1 forward + 1 back)
- [ ] Door opening animation = loading mask (define minimum animation time for loading budget)
- [ ] Preloading: begin loading next car when player enters 2nd half of current car
- [ ] Backtracking: keep previous car loaded until 2nd car back is requested
- [ ] Memory budget per car: define max based on target hardware
- [ ] LOD strategy for visible-but-not-entered cars (through windows, over rooftops)

### 15.4 Performance Budgets — P1
- [ ] Target framerate: 60fps on defined minimum spec
- [ ] Define minimum spec hardware
- [ ] Define recommended spec hardware
- [ ] Per-car polygon budget
- [ ] Per-car texture memory budget
- [ ] Maximum concurrent NPCs per car
- [ ] Maximum concurrent particle effects per car
- [ ] Draw call budget
- [ ] Physics object limit per car

### 15.5 Networking & Steam — P1  `  
